// Adversarial: Dead Man's Hand evolution chip (Damage Boost x3 + Last Stand) is injected via
// chip_selections. DMH fires its on-death effect when the last bolt is lost, applying a large
// damage modifier and potentially spawning additional effects. Fortress layout with chaos 0.1
// keeps the breaker nearly stationary — low action probability maximises bolt loss events as
// the breaker fails to intercept the bolt. This drives repeated death-trigger cycles through
// the BoltLost path so the DMH on-death chain fires multiple times across 10000 frames.
// The adversarial risk: if DMH's death effect incorrectly re-arms after firing, ActiveSpeedBoosts
// or similar stat components accumulate without being reversed, causing speed divergence.
// NoEntityLeaks catches any death-trigger entities left behind after the chain fires.
// NoNaN guards against multiplier overflow if DamageBoost stacks unchecked. BoltSpeedAccurate
// catches speed-floor violations from corrupted speed multipliers after repeated bolt-loss cycles.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Fortress",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.1)),
    max_frames: 10000,
    disallowed_failures: [NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN, BoltSpeedAccurate],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 1984,
    chip_selections: ["Dead Man's Hand"],
)
